<h2>Breaking Down the Basics</h2>
<h3 id=3D"what-is-a-hectare">What is a hectare?</h3>
<p>A  hectare (symbol: ha) is the metric unit of area widely used around th=
e world, particularly in agriculture and land planning.</p>
<ol>
  <li>1 hectare =3D 10,000 square metres</li>
  <li>Equivalent to a square with sides of 100  metres.<br>
  </li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"what-is-an-acre">What is an Acre?</h3>
<p>An acre  is a traditional unit of land measurement used in countries lik=
e the United  States, UK, India, and Canada.</p>
<ol>
  <li>1  acre =3D 4,046.8564224 square metres<strong><br>
  </strong></li>
</ol>
